{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"de407e02-fb8b-4424-ad7f-1acb10ae7559","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file compilation order matters** — files are compiled top-to-bottom as listed in the `.fsproj`. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`. The fix is to reorder them:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_AycMSqfhgrOc2XRsigXMdy","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-83d07d48fecb4551a09eca3e16b271bb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-83d07d48fecb4551a09eca3e16b271bb/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"5071961a-e19f-49e9-b1d8-288c9d173b75","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files must be listed in dependency order in the `.fsproj` file. Currently, `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`). This will cause a build failure because the compiler hasn't seen the `Domain` module yet when it tries to compile `Services.fs`.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile Include>` items so that `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":433,"requestId":"190D:24FEAD:13811B6:15DA78B:6A066E93"},"id":"e0db5625-4f23-436f-ae99-5696664013ae","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:47.087Z","parentId":"8226e8f2-27fc-4e35-b8ee-82f4c5477426"}
